spanGrp.span: In the olden days two old people, called Falea and Toukou, had six children.
069-001 Teetwei ipitlak tiawi inru rapitlak teesa ilates , nagi tiawi nranru nen ipitlak Falea go Toukou .
Our old people lived at Rentapau
§ 069-004 Tiawi ranru nen rapiatlak teesa ilates .
The first was called Apu Esel.
§ 069-005 Teesa pei nagien kin Apu Esel .
And Apu Esel was a spring of water.
§ 069-006 Go Apu Esel , ipi nsel nai .
The second child was called Apu Taf.
§ 069-009 Tekaaru teesa kaaru ipi Apu Taf §
Apu Taf is water which flows to the sea,
The third child is Ati Pako.
069-010 Apu Taf ipi nai nag iser pak namos ,
§ 069-011 Teesa katol go ipi Ati Pako .
Ati Pako is a shark which ran away
§ 069-012 Ati Pako ipi pako kaitok sef
Apu Sal, he floated and came to Erakor island.
Sal , ga isal mai tkal naur Eraniao .
The fifth child was Apu Tfer. He was a wave.
And the shark came floating and the wave picked it up and threw it onto the shore of Erakor Island.
§ 069-017 Pako isal mai go nao itp̃er kin ipak euut Eraniao .
The sixth child was Ati Aas.
And when the wave threw her on the shore she was a coconut crab.
§ 069-019 Go malnen kin nao itp̃er kin ipak euut go ipi aas .
And she became a coconut crab. She was there for some years, then she became a rock.
§ 069-020 Go kimai pi aas . Ito panpan
tete ntau rumai go kiler mai pi faat .
And the rock is there at Elignairo, on Erakor island.
§ 069-021 Go faat nen ito Elignairo , naur sees Eraniao .
And this is a story from the old people of Erakor,
who came from Rentapau to Erakor island. This small story is finished here.
§ 069-022 Go natrauswen nen ipi natrauswen ni tiawi nig
Erakor , § 069-023 nen kin ruto elag Erontp̃au mai tkal
naur sees Erakor . Ipi tesees wan inom esa .
